🚨 Brute Force Attack Detection Using Splunk
Worked on analyzing brute force login attempts using Splunk SIEM by monitoring Windows authentication events:
🔹 EventCode 4625 → Failed login attempts
🔹 EventCode 4624 → Successful login attempts
What I did:
✅ Identified multiple failed login attempts from the same source IP targeting different usernames.
✅ Used stats dc(user), values(user), count by src_ip to detect password spraying/brute force behavior.
✅ Correlated failed logins followed by successful logins to find possible account compromise.
✅ Built a Splunk dashboard with filters for Time Range, Source IP, and Username for quick investigation.
✅ Highlighted suspicious IPs like 10.10.5.200 and 45.33.32.156 with high failed login counts.
Sample Detection Logic:
Multiple failed logins → Possible brute force attempt
One successful login after repeated failures → Potential account compromise
This project helped me improve my skills in log analysis, threat detection, Splunk queries, and SOC monitoring.
